What's a "tooth trade?"
Amazing.
Oh. Uh-I don't know.
How much do we get if we work for you?
We're in!
We all want double-desserts today!
U-uh, Chef.
Chef!
CHEF!
We're not dealing drugs!
No!
Dude, having this much money is great! Working for Loogie rules!
We can't do that, dude. Loogie will kick our asses.
Dude, just stop thinking about it.
[noticing the silence] Kyle?
[notices] Aw, shit.
What?
Really?
So you're not gonna hurt us or nothin'?
We win again! [all get off their sleds]
Sleds are for guys.
Look, girls don't even know how to sled. Do something else.
You got it!
No problem!
Oh, boy! We'll show them!
Dude, this is horrible. We gotta get Cartman out of court so we can go practice.
Dude, if Kenny takes Cartman to Mexico, how are we ever gonna win the sledding race on Saturday?
[answers] Hello?
Son of a bitch!
Alright, guys. It looks like Cartman's not gonna be able to sled with us for another... 13 years, so in the meantime we need someone to race with us against the girls on Saturday.
Come on, who's the second-fattest kid in South Park?
Deal with it, dude! Cartman's gone, so now you're the fat kid.
Dah, that's what they all say. Okay, ready? Go! [he, Kyle, and Kenny push off and then hop on as the sled picks up speed. The rest of the kids cheer them on]
[looks back at Clyde] Nice going, fat boy!
Okay, we've figured it out. To add more weight to the sled, we're gonna use these bricks [points to them], but we're gonna cover 'em with kid's clothes so that the girls think it's another kid!
Come on, let's get it a try. [he and Kyle get on, and Kenny starts the sled and gets on,]
Yeah-
[to Kyle] Dude, bail! Bail! [they jump off, leaving Kenny with the brick rider. They end up face down]
[looks up] Ooh, my God, we killed Kenny.
We Killed Kenny. We're bastards. [they walk up to the tree and stand in front of the puddle of blood]
Nothing else is gonna work. [the rest of the boys converge on the tree] We have to face the fact that without Cartman we're gonna lose to a bunch o' girls.
You know something, guys? I think we all took Cartman's ass for granted.
That does it! We've got no other choice! We've got to bust Cartman out of jail!
I saw a movie once where they baked a cake and put a nail file inside of it.
Cartman, why the hell did you have to commit a hate crime?! We're gonna lose to girls because of you!
Yeah, you stupid umbassday!
...Yeah.
Sshh! [the guard looks over]
How are we supposed to give them to you?
But they're gonna search you on your way back to your cell.
Alright, here. [pulls some out and slips them through the holes one by one. The guard checks his watch and Cartman packs his ass]
Wow. I really wish I hadn't sat here and watched that.
That sucks that we couldn't give him the nail file. [pulls it out]
There's only one thing we can do. We have to go see Token and see if he'll forgive Cartman for hate-criming him. Come on, we're running out of time!
Yeah. You know, they bus in people from different races to our school to promote cultural diversity.
Yeah. [they walk up to the front door of a nice house. Kyle rings the bell]
Hi. Can Token come out and play?
[sees Tolkien] Token, you don't wanna see us guys lose to girls tomorrow, do you?
It's not?
Well, why don't you tell the governor yourself?
[to Kyle] Okay, go ahead and start.

Oh, uhyeah. [walks to the easel and clears his throat] Hello, Mr. Governor, and thank you for taking the time to hear our presentation on hate-crime laws, entitled, "Hate Crime Laws: A Savage Hypocrisy." [shows the title page. Kyle presses the play button for some ambiance] Yes, over the past few years our great country has been developing new hate crime laws.
[flips the page to reveal a person tagging City Hall] If a person vandalizes a government building, is it not because of his hate for the government?

[flips the page to reveal warring groups of people around a question mark] Mayor, it is time to stop splitting people into groups. All hate crimes do is support the idea that blacks are different from whites, that homosexuals need to be treated differently from non-homos, that we aren't the same.
That is our presentation. An idea that we call...
["Just wait. We got Cartman pardoned he'll be here any second. "]
Alright, where's Clyde.
Get on the sled, you fat piece of shit!
It's Cartman!
All right! Let's do this!
Come on! We've gotta catch up to them! [the camera looks at the slope. The girls come down first, then the boys]
We're not gonna make it! [Cartman thinks, then he remembers.]
We did it!
Yeah,. We're never gonna take you ass for granted ever again.
Dude, did you do all your homework last night?
I know!
Uh, Mr. Garrison, haven't you figured it out? Timmys' retarded.
But he is-
He doesn't have to do homework?
I've got ADD.
Dude, it's Timmy.
Yeah, Timmy ruhules!
But he's funny.
Yeah, what a dick. Timmy's five times more talented than he is.
Huh? No, we're not actually gonna take that stuff.
Because we're on Ritalin.
Oh boy oh boy.
But there are no side effects, Chef.
See what?
Let's watch something else.
Oh dear. Timmy's band broke up?
Yeah. Phil Collins was right. People laughed at Timmy, and Timmy should be at home, where he's protected from laughter.
Sounds good.
Oh my goodness, you killed Kenny.
Chef, are you going to the Phil Collins concert tomorrow?
Sure was, Dad.
Oh, thank you, Chef. How nice. [takes a glass. He and Kyle drink at the same time as Chef leaves]
I feel... different.
Wait a minute! Phil Collins sucks ass!
Get off the stage, Phil Collins! We want Timmy!

No! [steps forward] You see, we learned something today. Yeah, sure, we laughed at Timmy, but what's wrong with laughter? Just because we laugh at something doesn't mean we don't care about it. Timmy made us smile, and playing made Timmy smile, so where was the harm in that? The people that are wrong are the ones that think people like Timmy should be "protected" and kept out of the public's eye. The cool thing about Timmy being in a band was that he was in your face, and you had to deal with him, whether you laughed or cried, or felt nothing. That's why Timmy rules!
Why do we have to dress up? Isn't this just a circus, with elephants and lions and stupid clowns

Where? [a clown appears next to him, and he looks up] Oh, no. [the clown pulls out an umbrella and a bicycle horn, squeezes the horn and gets showered by the umbrella. The adults laugh, and the clown offers him the umbrella] Ha ha, very funny, thank you, goodbye. [the clown insists Stan take part, and the parents laugh at the sound of the horn] No, thank you. [the clown tries again] Go away, please.
Two hours.
Damn, dude. [...then the Eiffel Tower, and finally, a Tyrannosaurus Rex. The crowd cheers]
Damn, dude, do you see how much money this place is raking in?
Yeah. This one's moving out of town, so we could take over. [the boys turn to leave]
Dude, this isn't working.
Well, it's not good enough, Kenny! You have to get better! Try it again! [Grandpa rolls by and notices the boys in dance poses]
I'm tired, Grandpa.
I don't know. [walks over and opens the door] Whoa. [before him are the contorting Romanian quintuplets and their Grandmama, all shivering. Randy and Sharon show up in their pajamas]
Hurry up, you guys!
Dude, you're not gonna believe this.
Yeah. They're quintuplets from Romania.
Will you guys be in our Cirque du Celville?
Well, not yet. Kenny has to get better at singing first.

Okay, hold it, hold it. [climbs over Cartman and Kyle to form a tower. The quintuplets have executed their X formation. Stan is trying to stand when all three boys tumble to the ground. The quints break their formation and drop down]
What?!
[rushes up] Mom! Dad! Can the quints stay with us? Please? Can they?
They have nowhere else to go. [presses hands together] Please?
That's your dad?
[gets up and runs to his parents] Mom, Dad, you're not gonna send them back, are you??
No! We've just gotta convince these chicks that America kicks the ass out of every other country. Come on! [walks off]
Okay, let's try it again. Hup!
No, they can't! We've convinced them that they want to stay in America.
Now what do we do?
[standing in front of the still burning ruins of his house] Dammit, now I'm never gonna have my own circus!
The government came and got the quintuplets. No more Cirque du Cheville for us.
Yeah! Well, not this time!

We've just gotta get that angry mob back on our side! [addresses the mob] Alright, everybody, listen up! Those bastards broke in here and took those poor quintuplets to the mayor's office downtown! But they haven't won yet! I say we all go over to the mayor's office, and demand to see the quintuplets right now!
Uh, sure, you can all get overtime.
Hey! We wanna see the quintuplets!
[whistles a signal] Come on, angry mob! [the mob appears behind him. All of them move forward and overrun the checkpoint. A lagging protester runs over a fallen soldier]
Yeah.
Oh, well. Doing our own circus was a dumb idea anyways.
Whatever happened to Kenny?
Dude, I don't understand this game at all.
Um, deny it?
Sweet.
Dude, that's not cool. Don't give Kyle AIDS.
You don't pay tax dollars, Cartman! You're eight!
Oh, man, that's terrible.
Haha, he-yeah ha. [makes his own blow face] Haaaaah.
[does the same] Blaaa-lalalalalalala.
[looks and then faces him. Kyle follows] We're making faces at sick people.
We don't know.
You're not more mature than us, Cartman!
Yeah. Now what are you going to do?
[angry] We don't wanna go to some stupid adult meeting anyway!
Dude, maybe we do need to start being more mature.
We got invited too, fatass!
This is boring.
[to Kyle] That seems kind of... weird.
Yeah.
Dude! I think these guys mean to have sexual encounters with us!
Aah! There's more of them! Quick, hide! [the boys run into room 1A. Mephesto shows up and leads the other look-alikes onto the hallway]
Well, Cartman, you got everybody into this, you have to figure out a way to get everybody out.
Yeah. You know, we believe in equality for everybody, and tolerance, and all that gay stuff, but dude, fuck you.
And now, do you still think that you need to hang out with older, mature friends?
[raises his hand] Here! [he, Kenny, and Cartman laugh heartily]
Dude, what the hell was that?
...Dude, you weren't drinking any milk.
You have to be drinking milk for that to happen.
[drawn out] He's fakin'!
Now, that's a get-well card! [the others laugh. Cartman soon joins them, but his nose begins to leak that white liquid again. He covers his nostrils and continues laughing]
Dude, you can stop faking now. We got a substitute teacher. [Kyle mumbles once more] Kyle?
Go on, Butters!
Butters, go on!
Dude, you really are sick, huh?
Uh excuse me, but, what do these toxins look like?
Wuh, have you ever actually seen a toxin?
What?
Those aren't toxins. That's the bean with bacon soup he ate half an hour ago.
Don't be a smartass?
Hi, doctor. [takes a seat]
Well, it's my friend, Kyle. I think he's really, really sick.
But I don't think it's working.
[overwhelmed] Die? But... Kyle's my best friend. In the whole world.
...I'll give Kyle my kidney, even if it hurts a whole lot; I don't care.
Who? [Dr. Doctor turns the sheet around, and Cartman's picture is on it. A close-up reveals that Cartman has AB-negative blood] Oh, shit.
Cartman, we have to ask you a question. A very serious question.
Kyle's in trouble, Cartman. I can see him getting worse right before my eyes. There might be a way that you... can save his life.
What Kyle really needs... is a new kidney.
His mom is trying all this Eastern medicine and New Age bullcrap on him, but it's obviously not working.
Alright. Will you donate one of your kidneys to Kyle?
But you only need one, fat boy!
Dude, one of your friends is goin' tuh die! Don't you see how serious this is?!
Oh my God!
Cartman, you are so going to hell when you die!
What the hell would you do with ten million dollars, fatass?!
Come on, Kyle. Let's get out of here. [they walk away]
You mean the stuff that tastes like ass and doesn't fight cavities?
Look, um... I know that you all think the earth and its natural healing powers can cure Kyle, but... the doctor at the hospital told me it can't.
Isn't it possible that these Indians don't know what they're talking about?
And that has something to do with their medicines because...?
Nobody wants to listen, Kenny.
I don't know what else to do. I mean, he could die, Kenny. And that means we'd never see him again.

I guess maybe I've always taken friends for granted, like they'd always be there. If a friend died, I don't know what I'd do. [Kenny gets mad, Stan gets resolute] Well, I'm not just gonna stand here and watch my friend die. Kenny, go round up all the kids in town who want to help Kyle! Round them up and meet me at the bus stop at 7:30! Kyle's gonna live! [walks away]
[checks his watch] Come on, where are they? [looks around. Three boys approach from his left: Kenny, Butters, and Timmy]
This is it??
This is everyone that wanted to help Kyle??
[quite disappointed] Jesus Christ! Alright, Butters, you take this medical book, and everyone follow me!
We're gon' tuh take Cartman's kidney. [the others look are shocked]
[softly] Okay, it's clear. [slowly opens the front door] Okay. Me and Butters are gonna go up and take Cartman's kidney out of him. Kenny, you stay here and guard his mom's door here with Timmy.
Sshhh!
If she hears him screaming, or comes out or anything, just... stall her. Alright?

Alright Butters, let's go. [they walk away and up the stairs, then down the hall, but Stan stops in his tracks] Uh-oh, Cartman's pig. [Fluffy is seen sleeping in her own little bed. Stan and Butters try to sneak past, but she opens her eyes] Sshh, good pig. Good pig. Goood pig. Sshh. Okay. [Butters accidentally steps on Fluffy's tail and she squeals in panic. This wakes Cartman, who blinks and heads for his door half-asleep] Come on, we gotta get outta here! [runs a bit, then has his back to the wall as Cartman opens the door and walks out] Oh, no!
Oh, phew.

Okay, here we go. [opens the book and leafs through. Pictures of the heart, fingers, liver, and cutaway of the male genitalia are shown. Stan giggles softly and turns the page to a picture of the kidney] Okay, let's see. Looks like if we cut here, and here...

...vein right, well- [brings out the saw] Well, here goes nothing. Help me pull his pajamas up. [Butters pulls the sheets, Stan the shirt, and something more is in their way] No way! Kidney Blocker 2000?!
You suck, Cartman!
God-dammit, don't you care that Kyle is gonna die?!
[despondent, voice cracking] There's nothing more I can do, Kenny. I've tried everything to save Kyle. Holistic medicine is gonna kill my friend!
[sobs] My friend is gonna die! He's gonna die and there's nothing I can do about it. [begins to break down] Oh, God, he's my best friend... [weeps]
Awgh! I'll never see Kyle again! [weeps]
So NOW can we take Kyle to the hospital?
That's alright. If you'll all help, I think I have a plan.
Dude, please. Kyle needs it.
Alright, alright, here. [hands him a bloody kidney. Cartman reviews it.]
You look a lot better.
Dude, you're my best friend. I don't want you to die until I do.
Kyle's all better, Cartman, thanks to you!
It was all a trick. Your mom undid the kidney blocker, and then we put ketchup on your bed so you'd think we took your kidney.
Hey, Mr. Garrison. Where have you been?
Careful, Cartman, you might pop your stitches. [laughs a long time with Kyle]
You don't even know what you're debating about half the time!
Uh... that, that's okay, dude, I think we got it.
Whoa, dude, I don't see anything wrong with that flag.
Islam??
Well, we need help with our debate club. We have to explain why we think the flag should not be changed.
Yeah, we don't see what the big deal is.
But Chef, we don't know what you're talking about, it's--
Come on, you guys. We all have to work on this!
I don't think we stand a chance in this debate, 'cause Wendy's leading the other side.
Yeah, you must be thirsty after eating 60 mints. [Mr. Broflovski enters]
Do you think they should change the flag?
That was a good one.
[recovered, looks at the flag] Wait, I don't get it.

Dad, we know how to destroy the Wall-Mart.
One of the creators told us. You have to take your keys over to the television department.
What?!
Come on, we've got to try to make it to the back! [the three make their way to the back, but Randy can't help but look at all the bargains]
Is that the right way, Dad? Dad?! [looks around, then turns to his right. Kyle turns to his left. Both boys see Randy] Dad!
Come on, Dad!
No, dad! We need your keys!
[passing the candy display] There! The television department!
You?
["We don't want your store in our town we come to destroy you. "]
Me. I'm asking the question.
Stan Marsh. Now, where's the heart?
It's a mirror.
Well, the guy in Arkansas said to destroy the heart. [the boys turn and face the mirror again, and Kyle takes a black mallet to it. It shatters.]

We'd better get out of here. [outside, Cartman and Kenny stop wrestling and witness the Wall-Mart rumbling and there's lighting flying around it. Inside, Stan and Kyle make their way to the front doors]
Dad, come on! We've gotta get out!
Kyle, Kenny! I have to talk to you right now!
[pulls Kyle away] Right now, goddamnit!
[the look of fear is strong on his face] Trent Boyett is being released from Juvenile Hall. [the boys are suddenly afraid]
Yeah! He just got paroled!
What the hell are we gonna do??
Dude, let's play Fireman.
Hey, Kenny's right. We should put out a real fire. Then we'll be heroes!
Start one. Then we're gonna put it out.
Yeah, yeah. We play Fireman all the time.
Wow, cool!

[walks up to the crumples sheet] Woo, woo, woo, woo. Clang, clang, clang, clang, clang! [drops his pants and begins pissing on the paper] Come on, firemen! Put out the fire! [the other boys come and imitate the fire truck noises while pissing on the paper. Trent looks on.]
We're heroes!
Put it out, put it out! [Cartman runs up to their teacher and starts pissing on her. Stan, Kyle, and Kenny follow suit]
Dude, we are in so much trouble!
That's true.
No!
Yeah, who cares?
Now it's five years later. And Trent Boyett is being released.
Shhh, here comes Ms. Claridge now. [a soft noise is heard, and in rolls a futuristic wheelchair, encasing Ms. Claridge]
[nervously] Are you having a nice day, Ms. Claridge? [a yellow button on the machine lights up and beeps. She turns left and rolls away]
Calm down guys, we don't have to go tell our parents. We just need to go out and get some protection.
I'm talking about hiring somebody bigger than Trent to protect us from him. Come on! [the boys run off]
Stay cool, guys. If anybody can protect us from Trent Boyett, it's the sixth graders.
We've come to... ask you for help.
Yeah.
What?!
Dude, weak!
[after some thought] No!
You see, Mom, all the kids at school were told to bring a picture of their moms' breasts for anatomy class.
But mom, my teacher will-
[normal] But Mo-o-o-
This is hopeless!
That's sick, dude! I'm not taking a picture of my mom's boobs!
No, you're not doing it either! We just need to find something that looks like boobs to take a picture of.
How do you know?!
All right, fine. [draws some nipples on Cartman's ass, checking the book to be sure. He then steps back]
Excuse me!
[steps forward] We, we got it. [pulls out the photo. The sixth graders ride up to the boys]
Dude, are we gonna be like that someday?
Hey, look. What is Ms. Claridge doing? [she's still in the crosswalk] Ms. Claridge?
Dude, what happened?
What's that?
We're dead. Trent knows we sent the sixth-graders after him.
No, no, we've just gotta find better help.
[looks down] There is... one person.
Shelly?
Shelly, you're my sister, right? And families... depend on each other.

Shelly [hesitates, begins to tear up] Somebody is going to kill me, and I can't go to Mom or Dad for help, so, you're kind of the only person I have... left. [begins to cry. Shelly notices, puts her bowl aside, hops off the sofa, and walks up to Stan]
Trent Boyett. He just got released from Juvenile Hall. He was sent there for burning Ms. Claridge, but actually, it was our fault.
We were only four years old at the time, uh. We du-we didn't think about the past coming back to haunt us then. We didn't think and now he's gonna kill us!
Admit it was our fault?
Hi, Ms. Claridge. Uh, we have s-something to tell you. [no reply]
See, Ms. Claridge, when we were little, we used to play with our wieners a lot, and one game we played was "Fireman."
Trent, look, we've realized our mistake! [Trent advances, the boys back up]
What is that?
Yeah, who cares?

Eric, it looks as though the school will be serving a chicken cutlet. Now, that's traditionally a uh-a white meat chicken... breast, if you will, that has been breaded, and then cooked. I've been told there will also be tater-tots and a vegetable dish. This is really shaping up to be a ah-ah one fantastic lunch. Eric?
[returning from the kitchen to serve as cameraman] And we're... cut! [turns off the camera]
Yeah, I think that was one of our best shows yet.
...Craig's show??
But that's... that's crap! That's not even TV!
Apparently it doesn't matter how hard you work.
[look at Cartman, but notices someone else] Hey, look, Craig just walked in. [Craig enters to cheers from the other kids in the restaurant and waves back to them. Several kids take pictures of Craig]
Your idea took about this much thought, Craig! [holds up a fist with thumb and index finger just a centimeter apart]

Token! Now, come on, guys! We worked too hard to just roll over for Craig and his stupid overall deal. Instead of sitting here feeling sorry for ourselves, we just need to figure out how to make our show better!
Come on, guys! [the boys leave]
All right, we all need to come up with ideas for our show.
Yeah, Sexy Action, that's good.
We have to appeal to all the students, so we, we need hot girls for the sixth graders...
Good!
All right, Sexy Action School News Team, it's time to go to work. Get out there and get some stories!
Eric, the outfits are even skimpier than before, leaving very little to the imagination. No doubt that if I were a little older, I would be aroused.
Then, let's do Tolkien's report on how global warming is going to kill everyone in the fifth grade.
No, Jimmy, the school is already dumb. We're just giving them what they want.
I knew we could do it!
Craig's new show?
Hey wha-b-but we gave it our best.
[stunned] I don't believe it.
Yeah. To save our show, all we need to do is come up with the best idea for an episode ever!
Come on, doesn't anybody have any show ideas?
Look, you guys, if Craig can do it, we can do it! Come on! [time passes. Stan begins to pace the floor again] How about we do... a show... with us... ughhh.
Crab people?
[looks at Cartman, then gets annoyed] Dude, I think we can do a little better than crab people.
We're hopelessly stuck, completely out of ideas.
[reaches out and grabs one, then steps back] How about this one? Calminex? [reads the label] "Warning: Taking more than the recommended amount can cause severe side effects."
Uh, yeah, we need to come up with some ideas and inspiration, so we're gonna drink a bunch of cough medicine.
I guess we'll just take all of 'em.
It's... it's the greatest show of all time.
You guys. You guys, wake up! [the boys are roused]
We took a bunch of cough medicine to come up with ideas for our show. I didn't come up with anything.
You guys, we watched Craig's show all night long.

No, but don't you see? We didn't think it was great before. I think I understand now. [strokes his chin] I think I know why Craig's show gets such great ratings! Half the school is high on cough medicine!

[voice over] They're doing it in the hallways! [a shot of Tweek downing some cough syrup, then jumping in surprise with his iconic yelp and running away] Behind the school! [a shot of the Goth kids downing cough medicine]

Even in the girls' bathroom! [a shot of Bebe and Red in the restroom viewed through an air vent. Bebe takes a sip from a bottle of cough medicine, gives it to Red to sip, then notices something in the air vent]
[a shot of Jimmy and Principal Victoria looking at the report] We showed the shocking footage to the principal!

The cough medicine problem used to also run rampant in neighboring Middle Park Elementary. But they took action: riddled their entire town of cough medicine, and what we see now is a happier school, 100% cough medicine-free. [a shot of the hallways from the entrance. All the kids are coughing and walking around. Some of them sneeze]
[knowingly] Gee, what a coincidence.
Nobody has any ideas?
...Bail. [everyone leaves the table]
Oh, thank God.
Dude, I really don't think it's smart, Cartman. [Cartman is shown at the edge of the roof wearing wings made from cardboard]
["It's not gonna work just come down from there. "]
Cartman thinks he can fly off of his roof. [Kyle looks up to see what the others see. Cartman looks down]
[to Kenny] He's not gonna do it.
Dude, I really don't think that's a good idea!
[under his breath] Butters, Goddammit.
[a few moments later, sighs] Call an ambulance.
[walks by with a sled] What the hell?
It's... nice.
Okay, okay.
[doesn't smile] Uh, no thanks, I'm gonna go home. [turns around, picks up the reins on his sled and walks off]
Woof.
Oh, whatta? [squeezes his eyelids shut]
[irritated, grabs his clock] What time is it?!
[sighs] You guys, I have to go to school tomorrow.
...What?
[as they sing] All right, I'm going now. [He ambles off. A roar is heard nearby. All stop and look. The critters scream.]
Go away! Shoo! [The lion moves off and the critters return.]
Again?
Goddammit, this is fucking ridiculous!

[gesturing] Grrr! Grrr! Come on out! [The lion is heard roaring from inside the cave, and it roars. It approaches the entrance.] Come on, critter killer! Your days of slaughtering innocent little animals are over! Rawrrrrr! [Anticipating the lion's leap, he runs off. The lion lunges at him, but misses. Stan moves to the side of the peak and turns, gesturing.] Rawrrrrr! [Stan runs up the side of the peak, and the lion follows. Stan reaches the peak and turns to face the lion. The lion lunges at Stan again. Stan drops out of the way and the lion goes over the peak and onto its death below, at the cave entrance.]
Okay, there. [three lion cubs approach the entrance]
[at a loss for words] I... the... critters. Their... bir-birth of a Savior? [The cubs snuggle close to their mom's body, sobbing.]
[turns away and squeezes his eyes shut] Aw- awww!
It's dead.
I'm sure. It won't be hurting you anymore.
Wait, wha-what?
Wai-wait, the Antichrist?? You said she was giving birth to your savior!
But I thought you meant the Son of God!
Ugh.
Uuugh!
[waves the narrator away and leaves his desk] No, no-no-no.
Leave me alone!!
All right, all right, all right! God! [He turns off the TV, hops off the sofa and walks out the door, leaving the remote control on the floor.]
I'm not a heathen! I was baptized and my family's Christian!
No! I'm not doing you anymore favors and I'm not letting you give birth to the Antichrist! [walks off] I came here to put a stop to all this!

Right, whatever. [turns around] I'm taking down the manger I built. [Beary's eyes turn red and brighten. A wall of hellfire appears before Stan.] Ah! [The wall gets higher.] Aaaah! [All the critters' eyes are flashing a bright red. Black crows swoop down and attack Stan.] Aagh! Aaaahh! [A two-headed demon dog appears snarling at him; he runs off in terror.] AAAAAAAH! AAAAAAAH! [The critters' eyes revert back to normal.]
Oh yeah.
Hello? Anybody in there? [the three cubs appear at the entrance of the cave]
Look, I'm sorry I killed your mom. The, the squirrel told me she was evil.
I'm trying to make this all right again, but the only thing that can stop devil-worshiping critters is a mountain lion!
Well, you're mountain lions.
There still has to be a way for you to kill the porcupine's baby.
[cross] What?!
No, he didn't.
No, he didn't!
No, he didn't!
Oh, Goddammit! [the doctor and patient are startled]
I don't know, I- I'm supposed to show these mountain lions how an abortion is performed or something, I... I know, it's ridiculous.
This better have a point, dude. This really better have a point.
Okay, come on, the critters are over this way. You mountain lions ready to stop the Antichrist from being born?
Too late?! The hell is that?!
It's Critter Christmas, dude! It sucks ass!

[turns to the lion cubs] That's it?! Ten thousand years of darkness and I don't even have a Merry Christmas?! [Skunky, Squirrely, Beary, and Chickadee-y walk over to get Kyle. Santa's sleigh appears in the sky.]
I mean, I didn't mean to help them, I... I tried to stop them!
Dude, what the- ? [Squirrely activates his demon power with the red glow from his eyes and a wall of hellfire appears before Santa.]
[goes to untie Kyle from the altar] Come on, dude. [Santa continues firing at the remaining critters. Porcupiney is blown apart, then Foxy.]
What?! Kyle?!
Dude!
No, it all worked out, right? The world was saved and I went home for Christmas dinner.
Well, after all that, I at least wanna know if I had a merry Christmas or if darkness rules the Earth.
Well what did you expect, dude? It's the son of the Devil.
No Santa, don't!
The lion cubs!
I took them to see how abortions are done.
Now cubs, do like they showed you. Hurry up fast! Get the Antichrist out of my friend Kyle's ass!
[smiles] Yeah. Yeah, there is.
[relieved] Oh, good.
Dude, don't be nervous.
You're the best player at our school, dude. You'll make the team for sure.

Good luck. [Kyle reaches center court and is flanked by tall black players on either side. He looks around, seeing how much taller these players are than he. Two of them have basketballs; Kyle has his own ball]

Dude, you were awesome, Kyle. [no response. Stan looks at Kenny, then looks back at Kyle] Look, y-you gave it your best shot, right? That's all you could do. [looks at Kenny, shrugs, and walks away. Kenny walks over, puts his hand on Kyle's shoulder for consolation, then walks away. Cartman looks a bit concerned, walks over to Kyle... and taunts him!]
Kyle, you have to cheer up, dude. So you aren't built right for basketball.
Wha-a-a negroplasty??
Uh excuse me, is this really a good idea?
What?
Jesus Christ, dude!
Dude, is Kyle's- dad a- dolphin?
[points down the road] Kyle went down to play in the basketball game, Mrs. Garrison.
What?! But you made him into a basketball player.

Oh Jesus, he's about to play! [Three of the guards get into position at the top of the stariway aisle and start shooting at them. Down by the court Dr. Biber takes a steel trash can and bashes one guard with it]
Kyle, NO! [Kyle dribbles and then jumps up towards the basket]
Yeah, that's basically it.

All right. [the two parties meet] 'Scuse me. [holds out a clipboard] Hello, we are selling magazine subscriptions for our community youth program. Would you like to help young people like us by purchasing a subscription of your choice?
Who are the corporations?
Are you serious? We never heard that.
Well... Well what do we do?
Sign, sign everywhere. SignDone something to my mind.
Mom, the mall is a way for the corporate fat cats to imprison you into a life of servitude. I've got some stuff you should read.
Right, so how do we get back at them?
[alarmed] NO!
Yeah!
So it seems like we have enough people now. When do we start taking down the corporations?
You mean like a baker and a cop?
Alright, I can't take it anymore! I'm getting on that stage!
Uh, excuse me. Excuse me, can I have your attention please? What are we doing? [the crowd quiets down] It's been nine days! Doesn't it seem like we should accomplish something?

Maybe instead of complaining about corporations being selfish, we should look at ourselves. I mean, is there anything more selfish than doing nothing but getting high and listening to music all day long?
Dude, these people have no idea what's going on. Let's get out of here.
What? You mean, we're stuck here listening to this crap? [the stage is shown. All of a sudden the digger smashes into it, stopping the festival in its tracks. The crowd looks towards the stage]
Dad!
Token sings?
Wow, two hundred dollars. Can you imagine?
Yeah. We're too smart to be talented.
Hey yeah! We deserve that money just as much as he does.
He's looking at the sign.
All right.
It's genius.
[sitting Tolkien down on the sofa] Ohhhh Token. Right, yeah, you're makin' a smart move, man.
You guys, we're gonna lose our client. [the boys come into view again]
Look, Token, here's the bottom line. You're gonna start having a lot of offers comin' at you from all directions. A media storm is about to hit you and you can't handle it on your own. Nobody can.
This thing in Denver is is just the crust, Token. With our support, you can have the whole pie.
Ah Kenny, Token just signed with us!
Oh, you're interested in hiring our client?
You were awesome, Token!
This is just the beginning. I bet we start to see all kinds of offers comin' in for Token now.
[interjecting] Uh excuse me, Token already has representation.
So unfair... so unfair.
Huh?
You were looking for a talent agent?
And what does she do?
Uh, we're sorry dude, but getting her career off the ground would take too much work for us.
Yeah!
Hi, Mr. Lu Kim? Uh hi, it's Wing's agents. Everything's fine, yeah, but we're supposed to arrive in Los Angeles in about four hours. Listen, does your wife ever eat? Or anything?
Uhh, all right. We'll call you after she goes on TV.

Uh sure, here she is. [Stan puts the phone to Wing's ear, and Mr. Kim begins barking at her again] Okay, finarry everything rookin' up for me and my family. [outside there's a flash of light and three shadows pass through the doors] Welcome to Shitty Wok, take your order prease? [the men come into the light. They are three buff Chinese men] Aw crap, Chinese Mafia! [one of the men walks around behind the counter, grabs Mr. Kim's head with one hand and places a knife against his chin with the other] Aaaaahh! [the two men move around to the eating area and are met by four other Tong members]
There it is! American Idol contestants!
Ah our client has an audition to this show.
Oh no, no no no, come on! [the boys return to the attendants] Excuse me, ma'am.
No, I don't think you understand. We're here with Wing. That's right, the Wing. [the woman]
We can't wait in line! We have to be in school on Monday!
We have someone who's ready to go on TV right away!
All right, our client will do it!
What's "The Contender"?
Go Wing! [Kenny cheers on as well, but he's hard to understand. The bell rings. Wing's music comes up and she begins to sing "Fernando" as Fernanda sizes her up]
Anyone? Help four boys and a Chinese woman get back to Colorado?
Oh, thanks.
You do? [Stallone mumbles some more]
We won't! [Stallone mumbles some more, then leaves with his men]
You guys, you guys!
Sylvester Stallone wants Wing to sing at his son's wedding tomorrow! He's gonna pay her four thousand dollars!
Yeah!
Whoa whoa, wait, wait. ...where's Wing? [the joy leaves instantly]
...Oh Jesus Christ. If that big CAA talent agency finds out she has work, they're gonna try to steal her away from us again.
Oh no! [he points towards Wing, who's now being put into a limousine. The boys race over] Hey! That's our client! [the driver gets into the limo and drives off]
[walking up the driveway with his friends] Two four nine all right, this is the place.
Hello? We want to talk to somebody right now!
You tell 'em, Kyle!
Jesus, they really want Wing as their client!
No! Screw that, dude! If we keep letting CAA take all our clients, we're never gonna make it as talent agents!
We've gotta split up and find Wing! You and Kenny go that way! [Kyle and Kenny move away from the gunfire, Stan goes towards Cartman. Kyle and Kenny enter a blue room]
You bastards!
Yeah, you wouldn't kill her, 'cause then she can't pay you money! We know because we're in the same business you are!

[intervening] Guys! Guys! Guys! Don't you see what we're doing? Jesus... we're not talking about an object here, we're, we're talking about a person. I mean, look at what we've all become. All this violence and anger and, and for what? For control over somebody's life who... w-we're all just trying to leech off of.
Wing doesn't belong to us or to you. We're all just caught up in a business that treats people like commodities.
It's a lousy business. I quit.
I think we all learned it's best to leave talent to the talented people. ["Just sing..." Tolkien appears in the background]

[answering for Kenny] It's a game called "Heaven versus Hell." Kenny commands the armies of heaven against the forces of Satan. [Cartman walks up to the other boys, but he's quite upset. He crosses his arms] Dude, you see what Kenny got?
Yeah, Kenny finally found something he's really good at.
Are we in trouble or something?
Oh wow...
Please what?
What?
Kenny?
Dude, how'd you do that?
Yeah, the lawyer lost that page.
Now that Cartman got Kenny's feeding tube out, he's gonna die for sure! [they walk through the angels, then the angels turn around]
Yeah!
Let's go to the, uh, media. We'll make everyone in the country know that they're killing Kenny.
Don't kill Kenny!
Don't kill Kenny!
Well, what does it say?
Oooo.
You mean, Cartman's side is right?
[turns away and hides his face in his right hand] Aw Jesus, not again.
Yes! It's over! It's over!
We can start having fun again! [falls to the ground and rolls around]
We did it! We did it!
... What?
No... NOOO!!
Look, you guys, maybe it's not all that bad.
I know, but listen: the finals are all sudden-death elimination, right? That means as soon as we lose one game, our season is over.
I know we can lose if we try.
Okay, so then we'll just tell the other team quietly that we're gonna let them win, and then we'll act like we're trying. Our parents will never know.
Hundred bucks, no big whoop.
Uhh, hay guys, look, we don't wanna win, so uh, [pulls out a yellow sheet of paper] here's a list of all the pitches I'm gonna throw, in order.
Look! We're gonna be the losers tonight, all right?!
Damnit!
No!
[sees, turns away and hides his face in his right hand] Goddamnit... [the men have taken the fight to the field and are next to a trashcan. Stan pitches and the FC batter fails to swing]
Aw spit! [throws his mitt down on the mound. His father is arrested again with his pants around his ankles and hauled towards a waiting patrol car]
Oh no. No, no, no!
Dad? Dad, we need to talk.
[sighs] Goddamnit. [goes back into the restaurant]
I don't suppose you guys want to win this game.
Gay.
Hey yeah. We need to find the very worst kid athlete in the whole world. Somebody who can't possibly win.
Yeah, with him on our team, we don't stand a chance.
Wow, he IS great at sucking.

Dude, we had it all wrong. While we spent all our time trying to make our team suck, these guys practiced and got really good at sucking. [next pitch: the ball hits the bat again, and the SP runner has to go to first, as it's a bunt. Tolkien goes up. The pitch hits the bat at the top - another bunt]

[sees, turns away and hides his face in his right hand] This can't get any worse. [the two men continue fighting at the bottom of the level and towards the foul pole. Bat Dad picks Randy up and throws him over the railing. Randy bounces off a bench, breaking it in two.]
[comes off the mound and stands next to Kyle] Disqualified? [looks at Kyle for a few seconds] Fight! Keep fighting! [the fighting continues, and two more umpires enter the picture]
Come on, Dad! Get up!
Dad! [the guards let go and Randy turns around] You're the greatest. [Randy leaps for joy!]
[impatiently tapping the table] Dude, where is she? We can't wait.
Mom!
[twirling around] I want a breast!
But Mom, we've been waiting for hours!
All right.
Okay, this is everything, mom. [the boys return to their seats]
Oh, boy! [they see the denuded chicken pieces. Stan looks at Cartman in anger] Cartman, you ate the skin off of EVERY PIECE OF CHICKEN!
I can't believe that fat asshole!
Well this time he's gone too far!
Why do we even hang out with him, anyway?
Well it's not like we're nice to him. I mean, we rip on him all the time!
All right. Then let's just ignore him. From now on, let's not talk to him, let's not even acknowledge him.
I think I have extra.
Here you go.
Cartman isn't our friend anymore. [throws the football back]
Who was that?
Dude, he did that to me this morning.
Yeah, we know better than to think that.
Cartman?
Hey Cartman, that was really cool what you did.
Well, anyway, we just wanna let you know. Talk to you tomorrow.
He's what?? [Kyle shrugs]
A hundred dollar gift certificate to South Park Mall? [the kids begin moving out of the way, leaving Stan, Kyle, and Kenny] Maybe we should do the talent show.
Dude, didja see, Jimmy? They're giving away a hundred-dollar first prize for the talent show.
[bored, exchanges looks with Kyle] Woof.

It's gonna fucking work! Just fucking shut up! [take the shell to a stuffer] Okay! Okay, Butters. Look! [starts the machine] We're gonna put the stuffing in!

No! I'm not giving up!
Cartman, no! [follows Cartman inside with Kyle. Cartman prepares to drop the pangolin into the store's shredder] Don't do it, Cartman! That thing is our only chance!

You guys were right, okay? This hasn't been about Butters. I've been acting like this because I can't take these shutdowns anymore, and I'm scared what it's doing to me! [Cartman looks at him] I wanted to see that I could go out in the world and do things that I used to do, but I can't. I'm not any better, and I don't care any more than anyone else. And I did all this [tears well up in his eyes] because I just want my life back! I just want my life back... [begins to weep silently. Cartman's look softens. Recess is almost over, dude.
Yeah, we finally get back to school and have some sense of normalcy and you guys make the teacher walk out!
[turns to the boys] Do you guys know how hard it's going to be for them to find us a replacement teacher?
Okay, grandpa.
I don't even know what to do! If you ask me, this whole pandemic has been a giant waste of time! [leaves]
Yes.
Please, Mr. Mackey, we just want to get our old teacher back for everybody, okay? Can you just tell her we're really, really sorry?
Hello, sir!
Yeah, we assist senior citizens who need the vaccine, but then need help getting to the right place.
Holy shit, dude. That was pretty easy!
Just pay her, Cartman.
Come on, the pharmacist is coming!
Oh, great, Kyle. Now he knows there's a plan!
Kenny, grab the vaccines! [kicks the pharmacist in the leg, while Kenny grabs the tray of vaccines and they run out of the building]
Go, go, go, go!!
[angry] What the hell did I do?!
[walking up to Kyle] I don't see anybody. I think we're safe here until school starts in the morning.
[turns to look at Cartman] What?
I say we take the vaccines ourselves. I mean, why are us kids last? This whole pandemic has been about doing what's best for adults. Maybe for the broship we do what's best for us.
Kyle? [Kyle, startled, drops the can of Cactus Cooler and tries to hide the vaccine] What are you doing?
[walking towards Kyle] So then why are you replacing some of the vaccines with Cactus Cooler?
[angry] I don't want my mom to die either! I can't believe that you would lie to me. That you would hide shit from me.
[still looking angry] Yeah, we're gonna go to the school now, buddy.
[walking towards Kyle] I'm just gonna try and pretend this didn't happen. But only because it's what's best for Kenny. [he turns and walks away]
I just want this over with. Let's get these stupid things to the teachers and go home.
We don't have time for this, Scott. [the boys walk towards Scott Malkinson]
[grab the vaccines] We got to get outta here!
[glares at Kyle] And what about you, Kyle? You were the one trying to take vaccines for yourself this morning!
Look, let's just face it, you guys. We don't trust each other and we don't like each other. We can't keep pretending.
Look, it's been a hard year. And I think for some people there's just no going back.
We can't just force things for Kenny's sake. It's not good for us and it's not good for him. [he turns around, taking his hands out of his pockets and resting against the wall]
Yup.
A week is a long time for Kenny to be with one person.
It would be easier if I just knew I always had Kenny on certain days.
Well, I say that out of all of those... the first one makes the most sense.
[he gets out of his chair] 2-2-3. That's so ridiculous... that it just might work.
[walking up to Kyle on the left] Dude, what are you doing? You're gonna get yourself killed.
Okay, let's do this.
What the fuck is that?
Hello, Mrs. Nelson! [she is walking down the stairs]
Well, I guess this is it... [turns around to face rest of the boys]
Everything's gonna be okay, Kenny. I'll see you on Monday.
Hey, I wish you guys all the best, huh?
After everything we've been through the past couple years, they're gonna take pajama day from us, too.
What else can we do, brah?
We can do this!
There's only one black kid in my whole class.
I do hang out with him!
I... I don't know.
Uh, hey, Token.
Uh, listen, I uh... How you doin'?
Um... You think your family would wanna come over for dinner? Out at our farm?
Yeah but... Look, Token, I think maybe you and I should hang out more.
I mean, we never just hang out, you and me.
Shut up, Butters. Look, just will you please just see if your family will come over for dinner? It would mean a lot.
[to Tolkien] I thought your name was "Token".
Dude... my head is reeling, you're not gonna believe this.
Token's name isn't Token. It's Tolkien.
No, no, no, no. He's named after the guy who wrote The Hobbit and stuff!
[horrified] You knew it was Tolkien like the writer.
No, no, no! No, no, no, no! I distinctly remember Cartman wearing a shirt where he spelled it T-O-K-E-N.
Wha– hold on a second! [he calls Cartman]
Dude, Cartman, did you know that Tolkien is named after J.R.R. Tolkien?
Then why did you spell it "Token" without the "L" or the "I"?!
Uh, yeah, hang on a second Tolk-kien, just taking a shit.
Oh my God... I suck...
[returning the fist bump] Okay, I guess...
I kinda wanted to talk about something in private.
I think... I might be horribly racist.[pause]
So... there's this kid at my school, and... he's black. And his parents named him after the guy that wrote Lord of the Rings.
Yeah... well, I-I thought his name was Token. Like– like a black kid that's just there so that... like... there's a black kid.
The whole time! I've thought that the whole time!
Huh?
No, I was just try–
I'm sorry!
Doctor?
Doctor, please, I don't want to be like this! I'll do anything, just tell me what to do!

Guys... lately I've been doing a lot of soul searching. I've had to ask myself hard questions, because for a long time now, I've misinterpreted some amazing writing. I've done a lot of reading... And I've learned why Sauron built the black gate of Mordor across the path of Cirith Grogor, which led into the enclosed plain of Udun. I've learned that the Mouth of Sauron was once a man, who commanded the armies of Gorgoroth and dismissed Aragorn's claim as King.

I firmly believe that everyone would benefit from the school making required reading of these books. Because if we don't fully know about Tolkien, then we can make some terrible, offensive mistakes. In fact... did you guys know that our friend Tolkien, who goes to school here, is named after J.R.R. Tolkien?

[glares] My point is, we need to petition the school to make Tolkien required reading. To better understand our classmate. I think maybe we all haven't done enough to make sure than Tolkien doesn't feel isolated and left out.

[pause] Just a couple minutes, bro. [Tolkien leaves, closing the door]

Sup, guys. You know, I've done a lot of reading lately. And I'd like to announce that the school has allowed me to declare today J.R.R. Tolkien appreciation day! What are you doing here?

This whole time, I thought your name was "Token". Like... the token black person.
Yeah.

What?!

Dad!
But Dad–
Yeah, I got some right here, partner! [he gets out an air tank and hands it to his partner]
Dude, I can't believe we tied! That was epic.
And you know what else is cool? We all have teenagers now!
Hell yeah, dude! We just gotta keep our teenagers happy and we can play Airsoft all the time!
Hello?
[pause] Excuse me?
Oh, is this my teenager? How's it going, dude?
Well, you have to put the noodles in boiling water.
You… Do you have a sink?
Bruh, what?
Hey, man, it's cool! Lemme, uh– lemme slow it down for ya.
Dude, that's my friend Kenny, we gotta kill him!
Okay, okay, but if we kill Kenny we get a point, right? Come on!
It's okay, it's fine. We're sorry.
Dude, it's ok, it's just a gay rule. Come on, let's beat these guys!
[he takes his phone out and dials] Dude, Kyle, where are you? We started playing like 20 minutes ago.
Hair gel?! What the fuck, dude, we're getting killed out here!
Oh, my God, you gotta be shitting me. [Stan answers the phone] Yeah—hello?
Whuh—what?
I-I didn't call you gay.
I was saying the rule was gay. I wasn't talking anything about sexual orientation.
You're right, I shouldn't have used that word! Look—I was one of the first people ever to say there was nothing wrong with being gay. I had a dog that was gay!
Okay, dude… what… do you want me to do?
Okay, but you called me… hello? Hello?
What are you doing?
Okay, don't hold your hand over a lighter.
Jesus fucking Christ.
Yeah, that was kinda stupid.
I seriously don't know what to do… I've tried being nice, I've tried being harsh… and I get nothing from my teenager. Nothing.
I'd love him to threaten to do anything. I'd love him to do. Anything.
No, we can't give up on Airsoft—I'm like four hundred dollars into this hobby.
Except for the part about being around teenagers.
What do you mean?
Wow.
Alright, guys! We got the tents all set up.
So, what do you guys wanna do?
'Kay, yeah, we can do that later, but first maybe, um… let's bond a bit…
We… have completely had it up to here with you!
Our friend Kyle just wanted to play Airsoft. And now he's quit because of your attitudes. What do you have to say for yourselves?
Yeah, bruh. Great, thank you. [Stan turns around pissed] I can't… I can't…
And we don't want you here! We just wanna fucking play Airsoft without any of you on our team!
That sounds totally fine! Us against you, let's fucking go!
Fine, and you too when we beat all of you!
[Gerald, Randy and Stuart walk into the place] Dad?
They're not coming out of cover! I don't see them!
Yeah!
That was so epic!
That was so sweet, you guys! I bet the teenagers will never go back to that place again!
Yeah, thanks, Dad.
Ok, let's go!

[dissapointedly] Oh, yeah, sure...

Stop talking to me. [he leaves]
Yeah?

[Shrugs.] Yeah.
[Shrugs.] I guess so.
[At the entrance of the school.] Tolkien! Tolkien I need to talk to you.
Tolkien…  I owe you an apology. Someone has been messing with you… and it was all for me.
I’ve been jealous about you and Kyle’s TikToks. [Glass shatters. Stan and Tolkien jump. Students scream as Cupid Ye fires arrows to them in the hallways.]

Kyle, dude, where were you last night?
Well, yeah, we're all like level 12 now.

It's okay, dude, we had a great time.
...'Kay, well, we gotta get to class.[They all start leaving]
You say it.

Sure, you can play.

[from the living room] Ew!
You're playing "Hogwarts Legacy" on a PS5.
I wanna try it.
About what?
What the fuck?
Of what?
Dude, I haven't even said anything!
What?!
Dad, can I talk to you?!
I need to talk to you right now!
The fuck are you doing?!
You need to stop gloating to everybody!
Yes, you are, and now kids at school are calling me Richie Rich!
Nobody cares about your stupid toilet and you're acting like a jerk.

What's a plungercost?
I'm not bragging about my toilet! And why is it such a big deal anyway?
70% of the world doesn't use toilet paper?
So, then, why do Americans use it so much?
Well, then, maybe somebody --
Is he gonna be okay?
Dad, I'm sorry I yelled at you before. I didn't know you were really trying to help.
I let Dad down once. Somebody has to pick up where he left off. [he walks out]
There's something more going on here. I think my dad was on to something and I didn't listen to him, and now he's in a hospital.
Who will?
Second grade kid two years ago... Wrote about toilets in the school news paper.
You weren't warning me about people getting upset. You know more about this.
Hey! [he catches up to Jimmy] You wrote a story in the school paper and someone came after you.
Jimmy, I want to know who shot my dad!
You're talking about the toilet paper companies.
I can't believe they shot my dad... because he wanted to change things.

My fellow Americans, we have been coerced and brain washed. While the rest of the world walks around with cleaner buttholes, we are obsessed with dry paper sold to us by billion-dollar corporations.

And we can't be blindly buying their products anymore. And as a town, we will find alternatives, and we will not be afraid to -- [Randy walks up to the podium, interrupting Stan mid-sentence]
Dad!
No, dad, it's the toilet paper companies that are behind all the --
Dad, we can't just back down.
What about helping people and leading by example?
Hey, Clyde, can I talk to you?
Well, um, Wendy just came up to me and was acting all hurt 'cause she thinks I don't care about her.
Well, she says that she wishes I would reply to her texts the way that Clyde responds to Bebe so, like, how do you do it?
Chat GPT?
This is a real app?
Hello?
Didn't get what?
Oh, yeah, I- I wrote it. I'll send it to you right now.
Uh-huh.
You tell me what's going on!
You guys are using it to write essays, too!
You guys, I'm not going to tell anyone else! You really think I want Wendy finding out about this thing?
Yeah, it's really good.
For what?
Oh, that's cool.
Yeah.
Yeah.
Yep.
The boating accident in Switzerland... was tough.
It was great... and very tough.
Oh, shit. What time is it?
Oh, shit. My mom told me to be home right at a little after four. Sorry, Wendy. I- I gotta get going.
Okay, cool.
Shit.
That's not what's important. If they find out I've been using OpenAI for class, Wendy's gonna know I've been using it with her, and It's gonna crush her!
Look, maybe...Maybe this AI-detection technology won't work.
Mr. Garrison can I talk to you?
Yes it is important. You know when you done something wrong sometimes the best thing to do is to come out and admit it.
Clyde told me about it. I came to you because if they find out something me and you punish me it’s going to really hurt Wendy.
You do?
Yeah. Like a good writers assistant.
Yeah. So you really don’t think Wendy will be upset that I used ChatGPT to respond to her texts?
So you were just saying it was understandable….
Oh god o no no the GPT stuff on her phone didn’t come from her.
I don’t know what to do. I am not creative enough to think of a way out of this. Wait, that's it!
No what about her?
Hold it right there!
Look, everyone. We can't blame people who are using ChatGPT. It's not their fault.

I tell you who. It's the giant tech companies who took OpenAI, packaged it, monetized it, and pushed it out to all of us as fast as they could in order to get ahead. OpenAI is so powerful that it has to be something that everyone can use, control and contribute to, or else AI will be controlled by corporations who just want an unfair advantage like Cartman does.

We don't want big corporations deciding what is ethical and acceptable for AI. We were all taken advantage of and that's why my girlfriend will totally understand that I used ChatGPT to respond to her text.
You're welcome, sweetheart!
Boy, I'm sure glad that's over with.
Well, at least now we know that sometimes a good old thumbs-up from a human is better than a machine-generated lie.
ChatGPT, dude.
I didn't know kids could get jobs.
Love you, Mom!
I'm painting miniatures.
Whatever I want?
Can I see if any of the guys wanna come over to do "40k" all week?
You don't know "Warhammer 40k"?
Really? All week?
Sweet, I'm gonna call Tolkien!
Okay, so I'm gonna have my Retributor Squad attack your Stormhawk Interceptor.
Okay, so that's three, four, five hits.
We're playing "40k".
I thought you were happy 'cause the bitches were gone.
Okay, Dad. So I've got an Imperium infantry unit within six inches of Celestine, so they have a +6 save.
Dude, it's so awesome being able to leave "Warhammer" set up all night and come back to it in the morning!
What do you mean?
Hey, whoa, whoa! Don't touch the models! We spent a long time on this!
Yeah?
Yeah, as soon as we're done with this psyker phase. I have five psyker units.
Oh. Hey, Mom.
Aw!
